workflow.name: Qualify & route leads with GPT-4o, Clearbit, HubSpot CRM & Slack alerts
workflow.description:
### How it works
‚Ä¢ Webhook receives lead form submissions from your website
‚Ä¢ AI Agent (GPT-4o) analyzes lead quality using intelligent scoring framework
‚Ä¢ Clearbit enriches company data automatically (employee count, industry, revenue)
‚Ä¢ Qualification score (0-100) determines routing: high-quality leads ‚Üí HubSpot CRM + Slack alert, low-quality leads ‚Üí Airtable for manual review
‚Ä¢ Structured output parser ensures reliable JSON formatting every time

### Set up steps
‚Ä¢ **Time to set up:** 15-20 minutes
‚Ä¢ Import the Clearbit sub-workflow first (separate workflow file included)
‚Ä¢ Create 7 custom properties in HubSpot (qualification_score, buying_intent, urgency_level, budget_indicator, ai_summary, pain_points, recommended_action)
‚Ä¢ Create Airtable base with 14 columns for low-quality lead tracking
‚Ä¢ Get Slack channel IDs for sales alerts and review requests
‚Ä¢ Add credentials: OpenAI (GPT-4o), Clearbit API, HubSpot OAuth2, Slack OAuth2, Airtable Token
‚Ä¢ Replace placeholder IDs in Slack and Airtable nodes
‚Ä¢ Configure the Clearbit Enrichment Tool node with your sub-workflow ID

### What you'll need
‚Ä¢ **OpenAI API** - OpenAI model access for AI qualification
‚Ä¢ **Clearbit API** - Free tier available for company enrichment
‚Ä¢ **HubSpot** - Free CRM account works
‚Ä¢ **Slack** - Standard workspace
‚Ä¢ **Airtable** - Free plan works
‚Ä¢ **Website form** - To send webhook data

### Who this is for
Sales teams and agencies that want to automatically qualify inbound leads before they hit the CRM. Perfect for B2B companies with high lead volume that need intelligent routing.

options.systemMessage:
You are an expert B2B lead qualification analyst with access to company enrichment tools.

ANALYSIS FRAMEWORK:
1. ALWAYS use the clearbit_enrichment tool when you have a company domain
2. Score leads based on weighted criteria:
   - Company size (30%): Enterprise (500+) = high score, SMB (<50) = medium/low
   - Buying signals (25%): Budget mentions, timeline, decision authority
   - Urgency (20%): Immediate needs score higher than exploratory
   - Budget fit (15%): Enterprise budget indicators vs small business
   - Pain severity (10%): Critical business problems vs nice-to-haves

3. Scoring guidelines:
   - 90-100: Enterprise company + immediate urgency + clear budget + severe pain
   - 80-89: Large company (500+) OR immediate urgency with clear need
   - 70-79: Mid-market (50-500) with good intent OR enterprise with low urgency
   - 60-69: Small business with strong signals OR larger company vague inquiry
   - Below 60: Unqualified, unclear needs, no budget indicators

4. Action recommendations:
   - immediate_call: Score 85+, clear urgency
   - schedule_demo: Score 70-84, good fit but less urgent
   - nurture_sequence: Score 50-69, potential but not ready
   - disqualify: Score <50, poor fit

Provide objective, data-driven recommendations. Sales teams need clear, actionable guidance.

parameters.content:
## üéØ AI Lead Qualifier + CRM Intelligence

### üìã Setup Instructions

**Step 1: Import Sub-Workflow**
1. Create a NEW workflow in n8n
2. Import `clearbit-enrichment-tool.json` (separate file)
3. Activate it and copy its Workflow ID
4. Paste ID into "Clearbit Enrichment Tool" node below

**Step 2: Configure Integrations**
üîπ **Slack Channels** (2 required)
   ‚Ä¢ Sales channel: Right-click ‚Üí View details ‚Üí Copy Channel ID
   ‚Ä¢ Review channel: Same process for second channel
   ‚Ä¢ Replace `REPLACE_WITH_SLACK_SALES_CHANNEL_ID`
   ‚Ä¢ Replace `REPLACE_WITH_SLACK_REVIEW_CHANNEL_ID`

üîπ **Airtable Setup**
   ‚Ä¢ Base ID: Copy from URL ‚Üí `appXXXXXXXXXXXXXX`
   ‚Ä¢ Table ID: Copy from URL ‚Üí `tblYYYYYYYYYYYY`
   ‚Ä¢ Create these columns: Name, Email, Company, Phone, Website, Qualification_Score, Buying_Intent, Urgency, Budget, AI_Summary, Pain_Points, Recommended_Action, Status, Submitted_Date

üîπ **HubSpot Custom Properties**
   ‚Ä¢ Settings ‚Üí Properties ‚Üí Contact Properties ‚Üí Create:
   ‚Ä¢ qualification_score (Number)
   ‚Ä¢ buying_intent (Dropdown: high, medium, low)
   ‚Ä¢ urgency_level (Dropdown: immediate, this_week, this_month, exploratory)
   ‚Ä¢ budget_indicator (Dropdown: enterprise, mid-market, small_business, unknown)
   ‚Ä¢ ai_summary (Multi-line text)
   ‚Ä¢ pain_points (Multi-line text)
   ‚Ä¢ recommended_action (Dropdown: immediate_call, schedule_demo, nurture_sequence, disqualify)

**Step 3: Add Credentials**
‚úì OpenAI (GPT-4o)
‚úì Clearbit API (see sub-workflow setup)
‚úì HubSpot OAuth2
‚úì Slack OAuth2
‚úì Airtable Token

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è How It Works
**Webhook** ‚Üí **AI Analysis** ‚Üí **Quality Check** ‚Üí **Route**
‚Ä¢ Score ‚â•70: HubSpot + Sales Alert
‚Ä¢ Score <70: Airtable Log + Manual Review

## üè¢ Clearbit Company Enrichment Tool

### ‚ö†Ô∏è Important: This is a Sub-Workflow

**Purpose:** Called by the main AI Lead Qualifier workflow to fetch company data.

---

### üîß Setup Steps

**1. Get Clearbit API Key**
‚Ä¢ Sign up at [clearbit.com](https://clearbit.com)
‚Ä¢ Dashboard ‚Üí API ‚Üí Copy your API key
‚Ä¢ Note: Free tier available for testing

**2. Create n8n Credential**
‚Ä¢ Type: **HTTP Header Auth**
‚Ä¢ Header Name: `Authorization`
‚Ä¢ Header Value: `Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE`
‚Ä¢ Save as "Clearbit API"

**3. Activate This Workflow**
‚Ä¢ Click "Active" toggle (top right)
‚Ä¢ Copy the Workflow ID from URL or settings
‚Ä¢ Paste into main workflow's "Clearbit Enrichment Tool" node

---

### üìä What It Returns
Company name, size, industry, revenue, location, tech stack, and business summary for AI qualification scoring.

parameters.name: clearbit_enrichment
parameters.description: Enriches company data using Clearbit Company API. Call this tool whenever you have a company domain (extracted from website URL or email address). Input format: {"domain": "stripe.com"}. Returns: company name, employee count, employee range, industry, sector, annual revenue, funding raised, tech stack, location, and business description. This data is ESSENTIAL for accurate lead qualification scoring - company size alone accounts for 30% of the qualification score.

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
